🔹 TaskManager kya hai?
TaskManager SailPoint ka ek core component hai jo tasks ko manage aur execute karta hai.

👉 Matlab:-
Task ko start karna
Schedule karna
Monitor karna
Stop / cancel karna
Ye sab kaam TaskManager karta hai.

🔹TaskManager ke andar kya hota hai?
1️⃣ Task launch karne ke methods
run(TaskDefinition taskDef)
runSync(TaskDefinition taskDef)
runWithResult(TaskDefinition taskDef)
👉 Ye methods task ko execute karte hain

2️⃣ Schedule related methods:-
schedule(TaskDefinition taskDef)
reschedule(Task task)
deleteSchedule(Task task)
👉 Ye decide karta hai task kab chalega

3️⃣ Task control methods:-
cancel(Task task)
terminate(Task task)
👉 Running task ko rokne ke liye

4️⃣ Task status / monitoring
getTaskResult(Task task)
getRunningTasks()
getTaskById(String id)
👉 Task ka status check karne ke liye.

5️⃣ Task history / result:-
getTaskResults()
getLastResult(TaskDefinition taskDef)
👉 Pichle execution ka result dekhne ke liye

6️⃣ Internal components (andar kya hota hai conceptually):-
TaskManager internally use karta hai:-
TaskDefinition → Task ka config
Task → Running instance
TaskResult → Output/result
TaskExecutor / Handler → Actual logic execute karta hai
Scheduler (Quartz) → Timing manage karta hai.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ run(TaskDefinition taskDef):-
👉 Ye method task ko asynchronously (background me) run karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task start ho jata hai
Turant control wapas mil jata hai (wait nahi karta)
Background me task chalta rehta hai
✔️ Example:-
taskManager.run(taskDef);
System.out.println("Task started...");
👉 Output:-
Task started...

(chahe task abhi complete na hua ho)

✔️ Use case:-
Long running tasks
Report generation
Identity refresh
---------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ runSync(TaskDefinition taskDef):-
👉 Ye method task ko synchronously (wait karke) run karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task start hota hai
Jab tak complete nahi hota → program wait karta hai
Complete hone ke baad hi aage badhta hai
✔️ Example:-
taskManager.runSync(taskDef);
System.out.println("Task completed...");

👉 Output:-
(Task run hoga pehle)
Task completed...
✔️ Use case:-
Jab result turant chahiye
Testing / debugging
Chhote tasks
-------------------------------
🔹 3️⃣ runWithResult(TaskDefinition taskDef):-
👉 Ye method task run karta hai aur result bhi return karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task run hota hai
Complete hone ke baad TaskResult return hota hai
✔️ Example:-
TaskResult result = taskManager.runWithResult(taskDef);
System.out.println(result.getStatus());

👉 Output:-
SUCCESS / FAILED
✔️ Use case:-
Jab output check karna ho
Error handling karna ho
Custom logic me use
--------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ schedule(TaskDefinition taskDef):-
👉 Ye method task ko future me run hone ke liye schedule karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task abhi run nahi hota
System me schedule ho jata hai
Defined time pe automatically run hota hai
✔️ Example:-
taskManager.schedule(taskDef);

👉 Matlab:-
"Is task ko baad me chalana hai (cron/time ke hisaab se)"

✔️ Real Use:-
Daily identity refresh
Weekly reports
Night batch jobs
----------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ reschedule(Task task):-
👉 Ye method already scheduled task ka timing change karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Existing schedule update hota hai
Naya time set ho jata hai
✔️ Example:-
taskManager.reschedule(task);

👉 Matlab:-
"Is task ka time change kar do"

✔️ Real Use:-
Job ko delay karna
Frequency change karna
Emergency me timing update
-----------------------------------
🔹 3️⃣ deleteSchedule(Task task):-
👉 Ye method scheduled task ko remove (cancel schedule) karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task future me run nahi hoga
Schedule delete ho jata hai
✔️ Example:-
taskManager.deleteSchedule(task);

👉 Matlab:-
"Is task ko future me mat chalana"

✔️ Real Use:-
Job band karna
Unnecessary schedule remove karna
-------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ cancel(Task task):-
👉 Ye method task ko gracefully stop karta hai

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task ko signal diya jata hai → “stop ho jao”
Task khud safe tarike se band hota hai
Data corruption nahi hota
✔️ Use case:-
Jab task long chal raha ho
User manually stop kare
✔️ Simple samajh:-
“Bhai araam se band ho ja” 😄
---------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ terminate(Task task):-
👉 Ye method task ko forcefully band karta hai (hard stop)

✔️ Kya hota hai:-
Task ko turant kill kar diya jata hai
Safe shutdown ka wait nahi karta
Risk ho sakta hai (incomplete work)
✔️ Use case:-
Task hang ho gaya
System slow ho raha hai
✔️ Simple samajh:-
“Abhi ke abhi band ho ja warna uda dunga 💀”
----------------------------------------------
🔹 3️⃣ getTaskResult(Task task):-
👉 Ye method kisi aek task ka TaskResult object deta hai.

✔️ Return:-
TaskResult object
✔️ Kya milta hai:-
Status (SUCCESS / FAILED)
Error count
Logs / messages
✔️ Example:-
TaskResult result = taskManager.getTaskResult(task);
System.out.println(result.getStatus());
---------------------------------------------
🔹 4️⃣ getRunningTasks():-
👉 Ye method currently chal rahe sab tasks ki list deta hai

✔️ Return:-
List<Task>
✔️ Use:-
Monitoring
Admin dashboard
✔️ Example:-
List<Task> running = taskManager.getRunningTasks();
-------------------------------------------------------
🔹 5️⃣ getTaskById(String id):-
👉 Ye method specific task ko ID se find karta hai

✔️ Return:-
Task object
✔️ Example:-
Task task = taskManager.getTaskById("12345");

👉 Matlab:-
“Is ID wala task la ke de”
--------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ getTaskResults():-
👉 Ye method sab tasks ke results ki list deta hai

✔️ Return:-
List<TaskResult>
✔️ Kya milta hai:-
Har executed task ka result
Status (SUCCESS / FAILED)
Execution time
Error / warning count
✔️ Example:-
List<TaskResult> results = taskManager.getTaskResults();

for(TaskResult r : results){
    System.out.println(r.getName() + " -> " + r.getStatus());
}
✔️ Use case:-
Admin dashboard
History check
Audit / logs
----------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ getLastResult(TaskDefinition taskDef):-
👉 Ye method specific task ka last (latest) result deta hai

✔️ Return:-
TaskResult
✔️ Kya milta hai:-
Last execution ka status
Last run ka data
✔️ Example:-
TaskResult result = taskManager.getLastResult(taskDef);
System.out.println(result.getStatus());
✔️ Use case:-
Check last run successful tha ya nahi
Conditional logic (retry etc.)
---------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ getTasks():-
👉 Ye method system me available sab tasks ki list deta hai (running ya complete, dono)

✔️ Return:-
List<Task>
✔️ Use case:-
Admin dashboard me sab tasks dikhane ke liye
History + monitoring
✔️ Example:-
List<Task> allTasks = taskManager.getTasks();
for(Task t : allTasks){
    System.out.println(t.getName() + " -> " + t.getStatus());
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ getTaskDefinitions():-
👉 Ye method sab task definitions ko return karta hai

✔️ Kya hai TaskDefinition:-
Task ka blueprint / configuration
Name, category, schedule, handler info sab hota hai
✔️ Return:-
List<TaskDefinition>
✔️ Example:-
List<TaskDefinition> defs = taskManager.getTaskDefinitions();
for(TaskDefinition d : defs){
    System.out.println(d.getName() + " -> " + d.getCategory());
}
✔️ Use case:-
UI me dropdown / list dikhana
Developer check kaam ke liye
------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 3️⃣ getScheduledTasks():-
👉 Ye method currently scheduled tasks ki list deta hai

✔️ Return:-
List<Task>
✔️ Example:-
List<Task> scheduled = taskManager.getScheduledTasks();
for(Task t : scheduled){
    System.out.println(t.getName() + " -> " + t.getNextRunTime());
}
✔️ Use case:-
Automation monitor karna
Scheduled jobs ko update ya cancel karna
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 4️⃣ isTaskRunning(Task task):-
👉 Ye method check karta hai task abhi run ho raha hai ya nahi

✔️ Return:-
boolean → true / false
✔️ Example:-
if(taskManager.isTaskRunning(task)){
    System.out.println(task.getName() + " is running");
} else {
    System.out.println(task.getName() + " is stopped");
}
✔️ Use case:-
Conditional execution
Avoid duplicate runs
